      "message": "%X{BeginTimestamp}|%date{yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSXXX,UTC}\n\nI suppose the %date{yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSXXX,UTC} is a replacement of the %X{EndTimestamp}, which seems have go away.   The problem is that the supposed to be end-time is in UTC format, which is inconsistent with BeginTimestamp.\n\nThe comment is to keep both timestamps consistent.\n\nQuestion: What is the reason that the \"metricPattern\" is different than the transactionPattern?\n\nThe same question and comment would apply to the logback.xml in the feature-eelf project.",
      "author": {
